{
  "stem": "1895.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "More and more we had to restrict ourselves, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] until the time came when the rumors started, which was 1942 when the rumors started about deportations.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The deportations were-- I don't know who coined these phrases.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't understand to this day who coined these phrases.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But deportation was a euphemism for a one-way trip to nowhere.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You understand that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the word deportation denotes in my-- in my judgment, a change of address rather than going to a killing place.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So these-- these things-- we heard of re-settlements.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We heard of deportations.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the first action actually started in the city of Lublin.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it started in March of '42.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was the first city that was under the General Government, which means the Polish side of the occupation, that was emptied of Jews.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And about 40,000 or 45,000 Jews perished from Lublin.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But since the action that took place in March of '42 in Lublin, we started hearing these rumors, you know, that this city is next, and this city is next, and that they are emptying out and resettling or deporting Jews somewhere to the east, to the Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was the-- that was the-- kind of a delusion, you know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "People probably liked these names because they deluded themselves.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Nobody could believe that anybody could take 30,000, 40,000 people out of a city and just do away with them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Eventually I witnessed deportation in Radom.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But before that, when we heard these rumors, it also became known, and the Germans themselves [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] made sure that everybody in the ghetto knew, that there was a way of preventing resettlement or deportation.",
      "word_count": 38
    }
  ],
